This paper deals with a game-theoretic approach to power allocation in a frequency-selective interference channel, which involves information theory, game theory, networking, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.GT (Game Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
